<subSubSection id="127EAA4C1F61A78FD55283B9D28A441A" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="ED91C66DA4364816FDA46EB1FAD2CC95" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">The original specimens of the variety are still present in the Berlese Collection, viz. the nos. 208/26, 27 (type), 29, 30; they originate from Lake City, Florida.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8AA96A86E8F5D9D4471D4C542947898" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7C24DB85B7557DBBFEAC3ED5FB8DB8BF" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">The variety differs from the species in structure of tegument, colour, and size. In Florida the variety is, according to Jacot (1933, p. 242), more common than the typical species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
